Sign: Combine onion, celery, butter, and garlic in a saucepan. 
Sign: Cook over medium heat until onion softens, about 4 minutes.
Sign: Add flour and thyme. Cook 1 minute more. Stir in corn and potatoes.
Sign: Add broth, cream, salt, and pepper. 
Sign: Simmer 15-20 minutes uncovered or until potatoes are tender.
Sign: Garnish with chives and serve warm. 
